  <div>
    <p>Typography plays a crucial role in web design, affecting both readability and user experience. Well-structured paragraphs help organize content effectively, making it easier for users to scan and comprehend information. The careful selection of font sizes, line heights, and spacing ensures that text remains accessible across different devices and screen sizes.</p>

    <p>Proper paragraph formatting enhances the visual hierarchy of your content, guiding readers through your message naturally and effortlessly.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>Consider the spacing between paragraphs as a visual breath, allowing readers to pause and process information before moving forward.</p>

    <p>When designing for the web, it's important to maintain consistent typography throughout your application. This includes considering factors like contrast ratios for accessibility, responsive text sizing for mobile devices, and maintaining appropriate line lengths to prevent eye strain. These elements work together to create a cohesive and professional reading experience that keeps users engaged with your content.</p>
  </div>
</div>

